ts, 26,190; ship\nments, 4,280; stock, 50,551.\nI\nj Liverpool Cotton\nBy Associated Press\nLiverpool, July 8.\u2014Spot cotton in im\nproved demand; prices easier; good mid\n1 tiling, 28.12d; fully middling, 26.87d; mid\ndling, 26.62d; low middling, 2l.32d; ordi\n1 nary, 18.t2d. Sales, 4,00 bales, including\n3,400 American; no receipts. Futures\nclosed barely steady. July ,23.Sod: Oc\ntober, 22.26d; January, J0.79d; March,\nt 20.23d;Ma y, 19.76d.\nDry Goods\nBy Associated Pres*\nNew York, July 8.\u2014Cotton goods\n1 were very quiet in today's nvakgeL\n1 mills beginning to curtail their out?\nt put. Yarns, dress goods and men's\n5 wear were (lull. Silks were Inactive,\nwith one large concern in final dif-\nficulties. Burlaps were steady.\n1 SHANNON CO.\nBROKERS\nMembers New York and New Orleans\nCotton Exchanges\nCorrespondents\nS Tost A Flagg, 38 Wall St.,\nNew York City\nc WE BUY STOCKS AND\nBONDS FOR CLIENTS ON\nMONTHLY PAYMENT PLAN.\n212-217 Empire Bldg.\nPhones Main 322 and 323.\nLiberty Bonds Bought, Sold and\nQuoted\nProduce Market\nBy Aisoclated Press\nChicago. July S. Butter weak: cream\nery, 4Vrife>i^c. Eggs higher; firsts, 40^\u00ae\n41}fcc. Poultry, alive, higher; fowls, 8f)e.\nNew York, July 8.~Butter firmer;\ncreamory firsts, 52ty@67c. Kggs firm;\nfresh gathered firsts, 4VJrfM~\\&c. Cheese\nirregular, 26^027c.\nSt. 1x50is, July 8.\u2014Poultry unchanged;\nhens, 3flc; others unchanged. Butter and\neggs unchanged.\nTn the 'last 500 years Mexico has pro\nduced more silver than any other country\nin the world.\nHubbard Bros. Co.\nYork. Members New York Cotton Exchange\nNew Orleans Cotton Exchange. New York\nProduce Exchange. Associated Members Li*,\nerpoo! Cotton Association. Order* solicited\nfor the purchase and sale of Cotton and\nCotton Seed Oil for future delivery. Special\nattention and liberal terms given 'or con\nsignment of spot cotton tor delive\nCAMPBELL ORC j i\nCOTTON BROKERS\nSuite 217-218 Woodward Bldg.\nLocal Phone Main 6141.\nLong Distance 9955.\nFast. Direct Private Wires.\nCorrespondence Solicited.\nCOONEY CO.\nBROKERS\nMember N. O. Cotton Exchange\nCOTTON, STOCKS, GRAIN AND BONDS\nCorrespondent H. B. Beer,\nNew Orleans\nMezzanine Floor Jefferson Count;\nBuilding, Birmingham. Phone M i\nS. R. Stewart Co.\nMembers New Orleans Cotton\nExchange\nCotton, Grain, Stocks\u2014Private Wires.\nPrompt Attention Given All Business\nCorrespondents: Jno. F. Clark A Co.\nRooms 401-402 Woodward Bldg.\nPhoues Main 567 and 9388\nWe buy and sell Liberty Bonds.\nGiant Forces\nNow Affecting\nCOTTON\nPowedful factors influencing the\ntrend of Cotton Futures are care\nfully analyzed in our Comprehen\nsive Survey, just issued.\nA review of the elements respon\nsible for former Great Movements\nshould prove especially interesting to\ntraders owing the similarity of\npresent conditions, with the added\nfactors of Labor Shortage, Diversifi\ncation of Southern Crops and In\ncreased Purchasing Power.\nCopies may be obtained\ngratis upon request.\nMoss Fergus\nMembers New York Cotton Exc e\n1 Wall Street, New York\n\n7\nThe 10% Dividend\nEarned Twice Over In\nFirst Five Months 1920\nv\nt\nt\n\nV\ne\nr\nr\nFor the first five months of this year n*\nChurngold Corporation earned $6.42 per sh-.r\nover twice the dividend of $3 per share pei\n(10 per cent on present price of $30 per sha e\na dividend which the management has co.. o; a\ntively inaugurated. Dividends are payable month\nly beginning July 15th, assuring owners of stock a\nmonthly income.\nI\n\ni\n1 heChurngold Corporation\ni\ni acquired the capital stock of The Andrew Rohar\nCo. and the Ohio Butterine Company, makers o\nthe famous \u201cChurngold\u201d butterine and other fooc\nproducts.\nThe business of these companies has been estab\nlished for 20 years, their products sold in 27 state;.\nI through 8,000 distributors, production trebled it\nlast seven years\u2014during which time there was\npaid in. dividends to stockholders practically\ntwelve times the amount of their original invest)\ni ment.\nPlans are now making to provide greater planl\ncapacity to meet the constantly and rapidly grow\ning demand\u2014and this will mean increased earn\nings.\nA limited number of unsold capital shares o\nThe Churngold Corporation is offered, subject t(\nprevious sale, at $30 per share.\nI o appreciate the unusual merifcof this offering\nwrite us for full information.\nCHANNER SAWYE\nUnion Trust Building Cincinn\nMember* Cincinnati Stock Exchange\n$60,000,000.00\nARMOUR COMPANY\n7% Ten-Year Convertible Gold Notes.\nDated July IS, 1920 Due July 15, 19 0\nDenominations\u2014$1,000, $500, $100\nCallable at 105 and Interest\nCompany Pays Normal Tax of 2 Per Cent\nArmour Company proposes to issue $150,000,000, Class A, Common Stock, \u00bbu\nwhich $50,000,000 will be immediately issued, and $150,000,000, Class B, Comm i\nStock, all to be issued. Class A Stock will have preference as to cash dividends up\n8 per cent over Class B Stock, and after 8 per cent has been paid on Class B Stock be h\nclasses will share alike in percentage of dividends.\nThese note* will be convertible after January 8, 1121, par for par, into Class A Common Stock.\nThe company haa total aiscta of $490,000,000 and no mortgage except $50,000,000 Real Estate 4 V* per cent be *s\nsecured by part of it* property Not current assets are approximately $23,000,000.\nDuring last four fiscal years average annual earning! available for interest charges have been approximately\n000,000, not Including rbout $6,000,000 average annual earnings of South American subsidiaries. Annual inte\ncharges are approximately 97,500,000.\nMortgage will contain covenant that current assets must be maintained equal to one and one-half times all eon *at\nliabilities including these notes and any other Issue of not** or debentures at any time outstanding and any m *v\ngage indebtedness maturing prior to these notes other than purchase money mortgagee.\nPrice\u201494.84 and Interest\nYield\u20147% Per Cen